   About the Arctic Theme Page

   The Arctic Theme Page is a rich and comprehensive resource linking to
   widely distributed data and information, from research institutions
   throughout the world, focused on the Arctic. Available information
   includes relevant data, graphics, and forecasts, including historical
   perspectives and in-depth analyses. Also included are a selection of
   Essays by Arctic experts on key issues in the Arctic. The audience for
   the Arctic Theme Page is wide, including scientists, students,
   teachers, decision makers and the general public.

   Three NOAA Arctic websites are sponsored by NOAA's Arctic Research
   Office:
     * The Arctic Research Office website - Programmatic information
     * The Arctic Science Laboratory website - NOAA Arctic capabilities
       and science
     * The Arctic Theme Page - Comprehensive Arctic resource for science
       and outreach

   Questions or comments should be addressed to webmaster@arctic.noaa.gov.

